[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 7694,
        "end_time": 11534,
        "text": "Imagine as a thought experiment\nthat you live in a small village"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 11534,
        "end_time": 15102,
        "text": "and depend on \nthe local fish pond for food."
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 15102,
        "end_time": 18071,
        "text": "You share the pond \nwith three other villagers."
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 18071,
        "end_time": 23412,
        "text": "The pond starts off with a dozen fish,\nand the fish reproduce."
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 23412,
        "end_time": 27856,
        "text": "For every two fish, there will be \none baby added each night."
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 27856,
        "end_time": 30424,
        "text": "So, in order to maximize \nyour supply of food,"
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 30424,
        "end_time": 34266,
        "text": "how many fish should you catch each day?"
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 34266,
        "end_time": 36596,
        "text": "Take a moment to think about it."
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 36596,
        "end_time": 39847,
        "text": "Assume baby fish grow \nto full size immediately"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 39847,
        "end_time": 42866,
        "text": "and that the pond begins at full capacity,"
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 42866,
        "end_time": 46726,
        "text": "and ignore factors \nlike the sex of the fish you catch."
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 46726,
        "end_time": 50756,
        "text": "The answer? One, and it&#39;s not just you."
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 50756,
        "end_time": 53707,
        "text": "The best way to maximize \nevery villager&#39;s food supply"
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 53707,
        "end_time": 58437,
        "text": "is for each fisherman to take \njust one fish each day."
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 58437,
        "end_time": 60108,
        "text": "Here&#39;s how the math works."
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 60108,
        "end_time": 64734,
        "text": "If each villager takes one fish,\nthere will be eight fish left over night."
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 64734,
        "end_time": 67117,
        "text": "Each pair of fish produces one baby,"
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 67117,
        "end_time": 72187,
        "text": "and the next day, the pond \nwill be fully restocked with twelve fish."
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 72187,
        "end_time": 77499,
        "text": "If anyone takes more than one,\nthe number of reproductive pairs drops,"
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 77499,
        "end_time": 82408,
        "text": "and the population \nwon&#39;t be able to bounce back."
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 82408,
        "end_time": 85149,
        "text": "Eventually, the fish in the lake \nwill be gone,"
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 85149,
        "end_time": 88699,
        "text": "leaving all four villagers to starve."
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 88699,
        "end_time": 91859,
        "text": "This fish pond is just one example\nof a classic problem"
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 91859,
        "end_time": 94937,
        "text": "called the tragedy of the commons."
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 94937,
        "end_time": 97508,
        "text": "The phenomenon was first described \nin a pamphlet"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 97508,
        "end_time": 102177,
        "text": "by economist \nWilliam Forster Lloyd in 1833"
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 102177,
        "end_time": 104749,
        "text": "in a discussion of \nthe overgrazing of cattle"
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 104749,
        "end_time": 107788,
        "text": "on village common areas."
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 107788,
        "end_time": 112628,
        "text": "More than 100 years later, ecologist\nGarrett Hardin revived the concept"
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 112628,
        "end_time": 115358,
        "text": "to describe what happens \nwhen many individuals"
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 115358,
        "end_time": 118200,
        "text": "all share a limited resource,"
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 118200,
        "end_time": 119689,
        "text": "like grazing land,"
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 119689,
        "end_time": 120792,
        "text": "fishing areas,"
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 120792,
        "end_time": 121889,
        "text": "living space,"
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 121889,
        "end_time": 123940,
        "text": "even clean air."
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 123940,
        "end_time": 128039,
        "text": "Hardin argued that these situations\npit short-term self-interest"
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 128039,
        "end_time": 130249,
        "text": "against the common good,"
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 130249,
        "end_time": 132741,
        "text": "and they end badly for everyone,"
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 132741,
        "end_time": 134140,
        "text": "resulting in overgrazing,"
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 134140,
        "end_time": 135179,
        "text": "overfishing,"
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 135179,
        "end_time": 136489,
        "text": "overpopulation,"
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 136489,
        "end_time": 137560,
        "text": "pollution,"
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 137560,
        "end_time": 140760,
        "text": "and other social \nand environmental problems."
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 140760,
        "end_time": 143270,
        "text": "The key feature of \na tragedy of the commons"
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 143270,
        "end_time": 148600,
        "text": "is that it provides an opportunity for\nan individual to benefit him or herself"
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 148600,
        "end_time": 153872,
        "text": "while spreading out any negative effects \nacross the larger population."
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 153872,
        "end_time": 157107,
        "text": "To see what that means,\nlet&#39;s revisit our fish pond."
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 157107,
        "end_time": 159691,
        "text": "Each individual fisherman is motivated"
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 159691,
        "end_time": 162952,
        "text": "to take as many fish \nas he can for himself."
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 162952,
        "end_time": 165571,
        "text": "Meanwhile, any decline \nin fish reproduction"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 165571,
        "end_time": 168762,
        "text": "is shared by the entire village."
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 168762,
        "end_time": 171453,
        "text": "Anxious to avoid \nlosing out to his neighbors,"
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 171453,
        "end_time": 176403,
        "text": "a fisherman will conclude that it&#39;s in his\nbest interest to take an extra fish,"
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 176403,
        "end_time": 177242,
        "text": "or two,"
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 177242,
        "end_time": 178643,
        "text": "or three."
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 178643,
        "end_time": 182591,
        "text": "Unfortunately, this is the same conclusion\nreached by the other fisherman,"
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 182591,
        "end_time": 184043,
        "text": "and that&#39;s the tragedy."
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 184043,
        "end_time": 190419,
        "text": "Optimizing for the self in the short term\nisn&#39;t optimal for anyone in the long term."
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 190419,
        "end_time": 193303,
        "text": "That&#39;s a simplified example,\nbut the tragedy of the commons"
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 193303,
        "end_time": 197864,
        "text": "plays out in the more complex systems\nof real life, too."
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 197864,
        "end_time": 202783,
        "text": "The overuse of antibiotics has led to\nshort-term gains in livestock production"
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 202783,
        "end_time": 205023,
        "text": "and in treating common illnesses,"
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 205023,
        "end_time": 210003,
        "text": "but it&#39;s also resulted in the evolution\nof antibiotic-resistant bacteria,"
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 210003,
        "end_time": 212843,
        "text": "which threaten the entire population."
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 212843,
        "end_time": 216466,
        "text": "A coal-fired power plant produces\ncheap electricity for its customers"
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 216466,
        "end_time": 218563,
        "text": "and profits for its owners."
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 218563,
        "end_time": 221225,
        "text": "These local benefits are helpful\nin the short term,"
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 221225,
        "end_time": 226985,
        "text": "but pollution from mining and burning coal\nis spread across the entire atmosphere"
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 226985,
        "end_time": 229968,
        "text": "and sticks around for thousands of years."
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 229968,
        "end_time": 232108,
        "text": "There are other examples, too."
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 232108,
        "end_time": 233024,
        "text": "Littering,"
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 233024,
        "end_time": 234188,
        "text": "water shortages,"
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 234188,
        "end_time": 235495,
        "text": "deforestation,"
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 235495,
        "end_time": 236728,
        "text": "traffic jams,"
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 236728,
        "end_time": 239541,
        "text": "even the purchase of bottled water."
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 239541,
        "end_time": 245295,
        "text": "But human civilization has proven it&#39;s\ncapable of doing something remarkable."
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 245295,
        "end_time": 246785,
        "text": "We form social contracts,"
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 246785,
        "end_time": 248595,
        "text": "we make communal agreements,"
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 248595,
        "end_time": 250146,
        "text": "we elect governments,"
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 250146,
        "end_time": 251995,
        "text": "and we pass laws."
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 251995,
        "end_time": 257616,
        "text": "All this to save our collective selves\nfrom our own individual impulses."
    },
    {
        "index": 82,
        "start_time": 257616,
        "end_time": 262186,
        "text": "It isn&#39;t easy, and we certainly \ndon&#39;t get it right nearly all of the time."
    },
    {
        "index": 83,
        "start_time": 262186,
        "end_time": 266995,
        "text": "But humans at our best have shown\nthat we can solve these problems"
    },
    {
        "index": 84,
        "start_time": 266995,
        "end_time": 271337,
        "text": "and we can continue to do so\nif we remember Hardin&#39;s lesson."
    },
    {
        "index": 85,
        "start_time": 271337,
        "end_time": 273866,
        "text": "When the tragedy of the commons applies,"
    },
    {
        "index": 86,
        "start_time": 273866,
        "end_time": 277266,
        "text": "what&#39;s good for all of us \nis good for each of us."
    }
]